8 An Act relating to agriculture; amending 2 O.S. 2021,
Section 10-78, which relates to the sale of eggs;
9 allowing for sale of certain eggs in specified
locations; establishing limit on sale of ungraded
10 eggs; and providing an effective date.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 2 O.S. 2021, Section 10-78, is
15 amended to read as follows:
16 Section 10-78. A. Oklahoma producers of eggs selling ungraded
17 eggs from their own flock production are exempt from this
18 subarticle. Nothing in this subarticle shall prohibit the sale of
19 eggs produced on the farm and sold direct to the consumer on the
20 farm, at a farmers’ market, or otherwise off the farm direct to the
21 consumer. Eggs sold under this section shall be produced by hens
22 maintained on the farm from which the eggs are sold.
23 B. To be eligible to sell ungraded eggs pursuant to the
24 provisions of subsection A of this section, an egg producer in this
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB2110 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 stat e shall be limited to the sale of no more than one hundred fifty
2 (150) eggs per month.
3 C. A producer may sell graded eggs if in compliance with this
4 subarticle.
5 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
6 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON AGRICULTURE AND WILDLIFE
